    h2.mt2 Below are some of the most common attacks in the industry

    p.marginTop  Cloud One can protect against a multitude of different known and unknown attacks. Below are some of the most common attacks currently in the industry mapped to the different Cloud One products. 

    img.frontpageBannerimg.marginTop.marginBottom.floatRight(src="/img/hacker.png" alt="Cloud One Services")

    p.marginTop 1. <a href= https://www.trendmicro.com/vinfo/us/security/definition/denial-of-service-dos> <U><B> Denial of Service Attack DOS</U></B> </a> 

    p Denial of service (DoS) is a type of cyber attack designed to disable, shut down or disrupt a network, website or service. Typically, a malware is used to interrupt or inhibit the normal flow of data into and out of a system to render the target useless or inaccessible for a certain period. Please click on the button to simulate a DOS attack. For more information please look at our <a href=https://www.trendmicro.com/en_ca/business/products/hybrid-cloud/cloud-one-network-security.html> Cloud One Network Security </a> 

    p.marginTop 2.<a href= https://www.trendmicro.com/vinfo/us/security/definition/denial-of-service-dos> <U><B> SQL Injection</U></B> </a> 

    p SQL injection, also known as insertion, is a malicious technique that exploits vulnerabilities in a target website’s SQL-based application software by injecting malicious SQL statements or by exploiting incorrect input. Please click on the button below to simulate a SQL Injection attack. For more information please look at our  <a href=https://www.trendmicro.com/en_ca/business/products/hybrid-cloud/cloud-one-application-security.html> Cloud One Application Security

    p.marginTop 3. <a href=https://www.trendmicro.com/vinfo/us/security/definition/cross-site-scripting-(xss)> <U><B> Cross-site Scripting (XSS) </U></B></a>
    p Cross-site Scripting (XSS) is a security vulnerability usually found in websites and/or web applications that accept user input. Examples of these include search engines, login forms, message boards and comment boxes. For more information please look at our <a href=https://www.trendmicro.com/en_ca/business/products/hybrid-cloud/cloud-one-application-security.html> Cloud One Application Security </a>  and <a href=https://www.trendmicro.com/en_ca/business/products/hybrid-cloud/cloud-one-network-security.html> Cloud One Network Security 

    p.marginTop 4. <a href=https://www.trendmicro.com/en_ca/research/20/i/zerologon-and-value-of-virtual-patching.html> <U><B> Zerologon </U></B></a>
    p A new CVE was released recently that has made quite a few headlines – CVE-2020-1472. Zerologon, as it’s called, may allow an attacker to take advantage of the cryptographic algorithm used in the Netlogon authentication process and impersonate the identity of any computer when trying to authenticate against the domain controller. For more information please look at our <a href=https://www.trendmicro.com/en_ca/business/products/hybrid-cloud/cloud-one-workload-security.html> Cloud One Workload Security 

    p.marginTop 5. <a href=https://blog.trendmicro.com/cloud-transformation-is-the-biggest-opportunity-to-fix-security> <U><B> Cloud Transformation </U></B></a>
    p Nearly all data breaches involving cloud services have been caused by misconfigurations. This is easily preventable with some basic cyber hygiene and regular monitoring of your configurations. For more information please look at our <a href=https://www.trendmicro.com/en_ca/business/products/hybrid-cloud/cloud-one-conformity.html> Cloud One Conformity 

